UID:uKgfcnJcDj_qh8Z2WQ8g9
SUMMARY:Beyond the Cart Recycling Day
DTSTAMP:20260412T043239Z
DTSTART:20260418T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:Have stuff to recycle that doesn’t go in your cart? Bring it to
	 our Recycling & Reuse Collection event! Help celebrate Earth Day by parti
	cipating in this recycling event\\\, hosted by the PNA in partnership with
	 Seattle’s Waste Management. Bring paper for shredding\\\, along with any 
	of the accepted items (from the list below) that have been languishing in 
	your home\\\, waiting to be safely disposed! For more information\\\, you 
	can also visit Waste Management’s website. \\nAccepted items:\\n\\nFoam bl
	ocks (polystyrene only)\\nHousehold batteries (Both ends must be taped wit
	h clear packing tape. No damaged/corroded batteries allowed)\\nFlorescent 
	tubes and bulbs (no broken bulbs\\\, limit: 4 ft.)\\nSmall\\\, empty propa
	ne camping canisters\\nSmall electronics (TVs\\\, computers\\\, etc.)\\nSm
	all appliances (non-freon)\\nPaper for shredding\\nHousehold textiles\\n\\
	nItems not accepted:\\n\\nCommercial loads\\nFurniture\\nGarbage\\nYard wa
	ste\\nHousehold recycling (items that go in your cart/dumpster)\\nHazardou
	s waste\\nAutomotive waste\\nConstruction waste\\nNon-recyclable or reusab
	le items\\nCar seats\\nMattresses\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/r
	ecycling-day/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/recycling-day/
